A path relative to the job's workspace, where the source tree will be created. (Required)
The name of the Starteam project. (Required)
This can be the name of a single view or a ":"-separated view hierarchy as defined by Starteam. The hierarchy must start from the root view.

You can leave this blank if the path that you are checking out is the root folder. If you want to check out a sub-path within the root folder, you can specify that path as a "/"-separated hierarchy, starting from the folder immediately below the root folder.
You can leave this blank if you don't use labels.
This can be any option sent to starteam with correct spacing '-o -filter "IOGU"'.
The EndPoint is the port used by the StarTeam server. If not provided, use default port 1024.
Specifies the hostname of the StarTeam server. (Required)
Specifies the path of the file where the password is stored.
If checked, the StarTeam server takes the file as an encrypted file.
